        <h1>URL Shortener API Documentation</h1>

        <h2>API Endpoint</h2>
        <p>The URL Shortener API endpoint is located at https://localhost:7125/shortenApi/.</p>

        <h2>Usage</h2>
        <p>To use the API, simply make a GET request to the API endpoint with the long URL you want to shorten appended to the endpoint as a parameter. For example:</p>
        <code>https://localhost:7125/shortenApi/https://www.google.com/</code>
        <p>will return a JSON object containing the shortened URL, original long URL, and other details:</p>
        <pre>{
    "longUrl": "https://www.google.com/",
    "shortUrl": "abcde",
    "user": null,
    "entries": []
}</pre>

        <h2>JSON Response</h2>
        <p>The API returns a JSON object with the following fields:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><code>longUrl</code>: The original long URL that was passed as input.</li>
            <li><code>shortUrl</code>: The shortened URL generated by the API.</li>
            <li><code>user</code>: This field is currently not implemented in the api and always returns <code>null</code>.</li>
            <li><code>entries</code>: This field is currently not implemented and always returns an empty array.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Error Handling</h2>
        <p>If the API encounters an error, it will return a JSON object with an error message:</p>
        <pre>{
    "error": "Invalid URL"
}</pre>
        <p>If the input URL is not a valid URL, the API will return an error message.</p>

        <h2>Limitations</h2>
        <p>The URL Shortener API has the following limitations:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>The API does not currently support custom short URLs or user authentication.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Conclusion</h2>
        <p>The URL Shortener API is a simple and easy-to-use API that allows you to shorten long URLs. It is perfect for developers who need to shorten URLs for their applications.</p>
